			<h1> FORMULAE OF COMMON ACIDS & BASES </h1>

			<h2> Binary Acids, Ternary acids, and Bases </h2>
			Here are the names and formulae of some of the common acids and bases.

			<h3> Binary Acids </h3>
			Hydrofluoric Acid - HF <br /> Hydrochloric Acid -HCl <br /> Hydrobromic Acid - HBr <br />

			<h3> Ternary Acids </h3>
			Nitrous Acid - HNO <sub>2</sub> <br /> Hypochlorous Acid - HClO <br /> Chlorous Acid - HClO <sub> 2 </sub> <br /> Chloric Acid - HClO <sub> 3 </sub> 

			<h3> Bases </h3>
			Ammonium Hydroxide - NH <sub>4</sub> OH <br /> Calcium Hydroxide - Ca(OH) <sub> 2 </sub> <br /> Magnesium Hydroxide - Mg(OH) <sub> 2 </sub>


